metadata.name: A24Z #96
metadata.description:
Every artist and collector feels the joy of both creating and collecting. But if I could share the joy of creating with collectors. And collectors with their family and friends, what may be an additive process of joy is now perhaps exponential. Joy to the power of 26 to be exact. 

In this work I invite my friends and collectors to collaborate with me. Though not in coding, but together in a process of creating narratives and visuals. Code and story. We didn’t use github, just a simple p5.js editor to try out different programs and palettes. Pedrofe and J0rdan pick their palettes tastefully and carefully. okeoke, perhaps more of a genius than he lets on, picks his palettes blind. No hex color picker. Just straight up rhymes.  

In our discussions verbal language was forbidden. Only emojis were allowed to express our tastes and views. Each emojis put down on google doc was taken with absolutely seriousness. 

Pedro: Loves to taking his daily walks on “Magic Mushroom Mountain”

J0rdan: Wonders about “Quark Question Quiches”

Okeoke: Just get lost in “Finnegans’ Flower Fields.”

It has been a great joy to present our illustration book A24Z, 8 more than you know who. Each page expresses the alphabet with the best of our knowledge in semantics and sarcasm. Collect just 1 page, collect the alphabets that spell out your name, collect the whole A to Z. Read it to your children or loved ones. Though you might need to interpolate or extrapolate with great imagination which children all have. But most importantly, like all children, have fun!

Press 1 to save png, only for Chrome, not Safari. Preview images are compressed or broken, test capture at 300 sec.

License: CC BY-NC-ND 4.0

metadata.name: Traffic #69
metadata.description:
Traffic is a companion piece to Scaffold. Whilst Scaffold was intended to capture a moment in time of a single mind, Traffic aims to represent a shared moment in a community.

Outputs can be beautiful, but can also be chaotic. They can be comprised of many contributions, but a single voice may drown out many others.

All royalties go to the original minter.

Keyboard commands:

s - save as png
h - toggle high resolution 
b - toggle background texture
a - switch aspect ratio
r - new moment

metadata.name: Elementary Cellular Emoji Automata #568
metadata.description:
Features the full set of 1761 emojis, including skin tone and gender modifiers and all flags.
Arranged using the full 256 ruleset of one-dimensional cellular automata

If “random seed” is true then the seed of the generation is randomized using Math.random() meaning that the pattern will change on regeneration.
The ruleset, emoji, colors and all other properties will remain the same.

Auto-adjusts to screen size

Compatible with as many browsers and systems as possible

metadata.name: Disjoint and Disoriented #80
metadata.description:
Disjoint and Disoriented is about the abstract structure formed by the equalities and oppositions of its parts.

It might require high processing power depending on its features. A good desktop or laptop is recommended.

There are three render options available as url parameters in live mode:
- size=XXXX (up to 5760 pixels)
- texture=0 (disable canvas texture for print)
- shader=1 (use the shader throughout the painting process, can be heavy)

Created with p5.js and GLSL
dmarchi and lunarean, 2022.

metadata.name: Scaffold #42
metadata.description:
The thoughts we have are rarely as ordered as the words we speak and the actions we take are shaped by expectation and conditioning.

As we grow up, we are taught to behave or even think in a certain way. We learn what is acceptable and what is not. Our thoughts are forced to align with the structure imposed upon us.

Scaffold is an attempt to visually explore this concept of thoughts and control. Each output represents a state of mind at a particular moment in time.

Palettes have been mostly named by my family based on the first word they thought of when they saw them.

Keyboard commands:

s - save as png
h - toggle high resolution 
b - toggle background texture
a - switch aspect ratio
r - new moment

metadata.name: Lucky Oracles #281
metadata.description:
"Lucky Oracles" is part of the fxhash interactive minting experience at Art Basel, Basel 2022

Eko33, is a Swiss-French generative artist who has been at the forefront of digital arts since 1999 when he started writing code to create generative artworks and installations. He made his debut using a Commodore SX-64 and floppy disks. Since then, his work has been exhibited in Museums, International art fairs, and biennales. His work is focused on nonfigurative, generative art while using custom algorithms and innovative technology.

Official Website: https://www.eko33.com/ Official Twitter account: https://twitter.com/eko3316 Official Instagram account: https://www.instagram.com/eko33studio/ https://linktr.ee/eko33 "I create deterministic generative art based on crypto hash seeds. Maximizing algorithmic diversity."

If you want to receive an e-mail alert when I release new artwork subscribe here => https://eko33.com/email-alerts

metadata.name: Missingno #193
metadata.description:
Containment has been breached and Missingno is on the loose. 
This unique beast doesn’t have a fixed shape and its appearance is ever-changing. 
Some call it a bug, very few know what it is truly made of.

Only now with present technology we managed to capture a fraction of its unlimited possible faces. 

Mint for a unique picture of Missingno, yet outdated the very moment it’s taken.


(Open live and click on the image to export)
